President Biden and Prime Minister Kishida of Japan met at Camp David to discuss global and regional security issues. They expressed their support for Ukraine in its defense against Russia's aggression and reaffirmed the US commitment to Japan's defense. The leaders also discussed concerns about China's behavior in the South China Sea and emphasized the importance of maintaining peace in the Taiwan Strait. They highlighted progress on defense cooperation, including plans for a Glide Phase Interceptor program to counter hypersonic threats.